               <floruit> He was the founder of cenobitic monasticism. He was born of pagan parents in upper <placeName ref="LOC2804Egypt">Egypt</placeName>. 
                  His first contact with christianity occurred in <date>312</date>, when he was a conscript in the Roman army. Then, 
                  <persName ref="PRS7696Pachomiu">Pachomius</persName> came into contact with several well known ascetics and decided to pursue that path under 
                  the guidance of the hermit named  <persName ref="PRS7703Palamon">Palamon</persName>. 
                  Finally, he established his own monastery in <date>between 318 and 323</date>. 
                  </floruit>
